how secure is stanford's vpn stanford answers stanford university stanford answers how secure is stanford's vpn categories accounts and ids administrative applications anti virus and security computer operating systems connecting to the network desktop hardware and support email and calendar help desk restricted information on it services software at stanford stanford hospital and clinics telephones and cable tv unix systems and software web services user login login with your sunet id home how secure is stanford's vpn search this site the only secure aspect of the vpn connection is from your local computer to the vpn concentrator once you have been assigned a stanford ip address your system is on the university network and vulnerable to viruses and exploits windows users are strongly encouraged to visit the essential stanford software site and to download and install the following software prior to installing the vpn security self help tool a useful utility that can quickly scan your system for security vulnerabilities the software creates a report of any vulnerability and then gives you the option to quickly repair them bigfix a patch management tool that enables automatic updates of critical windows and virus updates symantec antivirus a critical part of the security tool kit install and configure for daily liveupates windows updates the recommendation is to configure this application to download and notify if new updates are available macintosh users are encouraged to visit the essential stanford software site and to download and install norton antivirus prior to installing the vpn virtual private network vpn is a remote access technology that creates a private connection over the internet between a single host and stanford's private network sunet see vpn at stanford for more information vpn virtual private network connecting to the network stanford university 450 serra mall stanford california 94305 650 723 2300 terms of use copyright complaints
